<!-- PG&E WILDFIRES -->
<article class="event" id="event-pge">
  <header>
    <h3>
      <time datetime="2017">2017–2019</time> — PG&amp;E California Wildfires
    </h3>
  </header>
  <p>
    Pacific Gas and Electric's internal inspections had flagged aging
    transmission infrastructure across northern California for years. The
    financial signal — deferring maintenance is cheaper than performing it —
    consistently won. PG&amp;E equipment was responsible for igniting multiple
    catastrophic wildfires, including the 2018 Camp Fire that destroyed the town
    of Paradise and killed 85 people. PG&amp;E filed for bankruptcy in January
    2019, the first utility in US history to do so citing wildfire liability.
    The mechanism — aging equipment in a drying climate — had been visible in
    inspection reports for years.
  </p>
